<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-425-052  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 425 052.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  April 30 1990 n298 p45(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SW Bell surveys customers; regional Bell aims to improve service.andO;(Southwestern Bell Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schultz, Beth.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Southwestern Bell Corp (SW Bell), with assistance from PorcheyResearch Inc, has been conducting customer surveys to garnermarketing information.andP;  Researchers conducted phone interviewswith 4,000 users and met with focus groups.andP;  The results were usedto establish a hierarchy of user needs.andP;  Currently, users are mostconcerned about technology and dependability, followed by ease ofuse, product guarantees and honesty in their dealings.andP;  As usersbecome comfortable with each level of the hierarchy, according toa Porchey spokesperson, they abandon those concerns for concernson the next level.andP;  Although service is a current customerconcern, as users become more sophisticated, they will focus oninnovations, customer communication and telephone companies'activity in local communities.andP;  The study also concluded thatcustomers are loyal to their local Bell companies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Southwestern Bell Corp. (surveys)Porchey Research Inc. (surveys).andO;Ticker:    SBC.andO;Topic:     Customer RelationsUser SurveyMarketing ResearchUser NeedsTelephone CompaniesUser BehaviorBell Regional Holding Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>